Interface ILayoutStage

    public interface ILayoutStage
extends ILayoutAlgorithm
    A ILayoutStage is a layout algorithm that represents a stage of a larger layout process.

    It delegates the core layout process to another layout algorithm. Implementing classes may perform pre-processing steps before the core layout algorithm gets called and post-processing steps afterwards.

    See Also:
    MultiStageLayout

        ILayoutAlgorithm getCoreLayout()
        Gets the core layout algorithm.

        This algorithm is wrapped by this stage. It is invoked in ILayoutAlgorithm.applyLayout(com.yworks.yfiles.layout.LayoutGraph). The ILayoutStage may add pre- and post-processing steps before and after calling the core layout algorithm.

        Returns:
        the core layout algorithm
